The executives of Tiger Golf Club Ibadan and the Local Organising Committee (LOC) of the Tiger Open Golf Tournament have announced a new date for the event. This was disclosed in a statement issued by the LOC headed by Col. Adamu saying January 16-18 2020 was announced as new date as against December 13-15 earlier scheduled. “We regret to announce that the Tiger Open Golf Tournament earlier scheduled to take place between December13-15 has been postponed to January 16-18 2020 due to unforeseen exigencies”, the statement reads. He added that “The Club regrets this painful decision but we are mindful of the need to maintain the high standard of this tournament achieved over the years by sustaining this enviable legacy.” The Club however regrets the inconveniences this postponement might cause their esteemed golfers, golf clubs, vendors and other stakeholders, while assuring them of putting in place a robust Tournament both on and off the Course.